  "intent_precise": "78d33c.ot2.apiv2: Using Reagents (labware, slot 2), Reservoir (reservoir, slot 8), output_plate (labware, slot Output plate at 4 Degrees C), mag_plate (labware, slot Mag Plate). With temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Pause: Please Refill the 300 uL Tip Boxes\n                     and Empty the Tip Waste (2) Pause: format (3) Set temperature to temp_mod_setting\u00b0C. (4) Disengage magnets to release beads. (5) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (6) Wait 1 seconds. (7) Transfer 149\u00b5L from source to destination. (8) Incubate for 10 minutes. (9) Engage magnets at height_engagemm height for bead separation. (10) Pause for incubation. (11) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (12) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (13) Wait 1 seconds. (14) Wait 0 seconds. (15) Wait 30 seconds. (16) Wait 0 seconds. (17) Pause for incubation. (18) Disengage magnets to release beads. (19) Transfer 16\u00b5L from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (20) Wait 1 seconds. (21) Incubate for 2 minutes. (22) Engage magnets at height_engagemm height for bead separation. (23) Pause for incubation. (24) Transfer from fragmentation_mm 0 to column 0. (25) Wait 1 seconds. (26) Transfer 11\u00b5L from source to destination. (27) Disengage magnets to release beads.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (temp_mod_setting\u00b0C). (volumes 4\u00b5L-250\u00b5L, ~14 min total)",
  "intent": "For this automated magnetic bead protocol, start by refilling the 300 \u00b5L tip boxes and emptying the tip waste, then set the temperature module to temp_mod_setting\u00b0C and disengage the magnets to release the beads. You'll be performing a series of transfers between the reagent plate (slot 2), reservoir (slot 8), the output plate at 4\u00b0C, and the magnetic plate - beginning with 200 \u00b5L and 149 \u00b5L transfers, followed by a 10-minute incubation before engaging the magnets at height_engage mm for bead separation. Continue with 200 \u00b5L and 50 \u00b5L transfers with various wait times (1, 30 seconds), then disengage magnets for a 16 \u00b5L transfer, incubate for 2 minutes, and re-engage magnets before completing the final transfers including 11 \u00b5L to the destination wells. Remember to pause for incubations as indicated and transfer from fragmentation position 0 to column 0 near the end of the protocol.",
